The paper deals with the analysis of a large dataset of open source software projects using Git, which is a version control system. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also uses community detection algorithms to identify related repositories, which falls under the social and information networks (cs.SI) and the software development (cs.SD) sub-categories. The paper also deals with handling large datasets, which falls under the database (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses machine learning algorithms, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
